ometimes the path chooses you.', 3620, 0), (48296, 'The secret is not following the right path, it''s following that right path to the end. Don''t quit, my friend, until you''ve arrived.', 3620, 0), (48297, 'The path back home is often the most difficult journey of all.', 3620, 0), (48298, 'You don''t get strong by standing at the finish line, you get strong with every step you take to get there.', 3620, 0), (48299, 'You will never get to a new place by walking an old path.', 3620, 0), (48300, 'Those who work hard and constantly seek to be visible to their superiors, those who showcase their hard work, are the ones who advance to positions of greater power and responsibility.', 11305, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (48301, 'Each daily task, is but the future in a mask.', 11306, 0), (48302, 'You thought it would break you in two, but it made you twice as strong.', 4574, 0), (48303, 'The focus should be on becoming a strong andinfluential personality – cultivate compelling communication skills, focus on building trust and learn how to expand and leverage your professional network.', 11305, 0), (48304, 'Many of us have this mind-set which considers self-promotion a taboo.', 11305, 0), (48305, 'In the present day corporate world, it is utmost important to build a personal brand for yourself and anyone who knows the basics of brand-building would know that it is impossible without proper self promotion!', 11305, 0), (48306, 'Move out of your comfort zone, develop those necessary skills and go all out for that much needed advancement!', 11305, 0), (48307, 'Use social events, social networks and every get-together at work to build a stronger brand YOU!', 11305, 0), (48308, 'We experience [procrastination] as fear. But fear of what?Fear of the consequences of following our heart. Fear of bankruptcy, fear of poverty, fear of insolvency. Fear of groveling when we try to make it on our own, and of groveling when we give up and come crawling back to where we started. Fear of being selfish, of being rotten wives or disloyal husbands; fear of failing to support our families, of sacrificing their dreams for ours. Fear of betraying our race, our ''hood, our homies. Fear of failure. Fear of being ridiculous. Fear of throwing away the education, the training, the preparation that those we love have sacrificed so much for, that we ourselves have worked our butts off for. Fear of launching into the void, of hurtling too far out there; fear of passing some point of no return, beyond which we cannot recant, cannot reverse, cannot rescind, but must live with this cocked-up choice for the rest of our lives. Fear of madness. Fear of insanity. Fear of death.These are serious fears. But they''re not the real fear. Not the master fear, the mother of all fears that''s so close to us that even when we verbalize it we don''t believe it.Fear That We Will Succeed.', 2339, 0), (48309, 'Accept the fact that you are fully responsible for your career.', 11305, 0), (48310, 'Freedom, I thought, comes only to the successful', 429, 0), (48311, 'Before you chase success, status, power, wealth fame or love; first fall in love with yourself - for the person you''ll be if and when you get there is still the same. Success will be a painful path and an empty trophy without self acceptance, self worth or if littered with self hate.', 4889, 0), (48312, 'When the vision is clear, the results will appear. Keep your mindset positive as you work your plan, flourish, and always remember why you started.', 2736, 0), (48313, 'Put time and effort to promote your personal brand.', 11305, 0), (48314, 'Resources don''t last forever. They must either be USED, MANAGED or they will be WASTED.', 11307, 0), (48315, 'I yearn not for the easy path, but for the right path.  For ''easy'' and ''right'' are rarely compatible.', 4397, 0), (48316, 'Take the easy road and at the end, you will feel you have achieved nothing. Try the difficult shit and you’ll enjoy your successes.', 11308, 0), (48317, 'People are more apt to respond to crisis, than to their dreams and vision. Dare not be one of them.', 11306, 0), (48318, 'Good advice for anyone wanting to make an impact with a product, a service or even a message is to differentiate yourself.', 11309, 0), (48319, 'May success knock your door always', 11310, 0), (48320, 'Nothing is impossible if someone make it possible.', 11310, 0), (48321, 'The greatest musicians never cared to be rock stars. They just wanted to play. The greatest actors never cared to be movie stars they just loved their craft. The greatest artists painted on canvas to fill their own hearts. It’s how we truly feel about things in life t